'''David Youngren''' (born September 23, 1962) is a [[Sweden]]-born speaker, author, former pastor and film producer based out of [[San Diego|San Diego, California]]. Before moving to the United States in 2005, Youngren served as the founding Pastor of World Harvest Church and Senior Pastor of Niagara Celebration Church, and was the President of World Harvest Bible College, Open Bible Faith Fellowship and Harvest International Ministries.

Youngren has staged Christian festivals in India, Russia, Albania, Ukraine, Tanzania and South Africa. Youngren claims to have experienced healing from [[cluster headaches]] during meditation in 2006 that led him on an evolving spiritual journey and a new direction in his life and career. Youngren founderd Juma's World, formerly SaveAfricaNow, a charity that helps orphaned children in Tanzania.

== Biography ==

Youngren immigrated to Canada from Sweden in 1981 to attend college, and subsequently began full time Christian ministry, primarily in [[Canada]] in 1986. He would later travel to [[Russia]], [[Africa]], India and [[South America]] for large-scale outreaches.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Arnold|first1=Lori|title=Reel Transformation|url=http://christiannewsjournal.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Chr-Exam-SD-09.12.pdf|accessdate=17 June 2015|issue=Vol. 30, No. 9|publisher=Christian Examiner|date=September 2012}}</ref>

Youngren founded World Harvest Bible College and World Harvest Church in [[Oshawa|Oshawa, Ontario]], Canada. Youngren served World Harvest Church as pastor for almost nine years.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Youngren|first1=David|title=Life From The Inside Out|date=2004|publisher=Harvest International Ministries|isbn=1893301214|pages=129}}<!--|accessdate=17 June 2015--></ref>

Youngren served a one-year term as president of Open Bible Faith Fellowship Canada in 2003<ref>{{cite web|last1=Neilson |first1=Randy |title=Beginnings... OBFF |url=http://www.obff.com/Newsletters/linkNovember%20Newsletter%202009.pdf |website=OBFF |publisher=Open Bible Faith Fellowship |accessdate=17 June 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304035346/http://www.obff.com/Newsletters/linkNovember%20Newsletter%202009.pdf |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df= }}</ref> before moving to San Diego.

In 2006 Youngren began SaveAfricaNow<ref>{{cite web|last1=World |first1=Juma's |title=About Juma's World: Our History |url=http://jumasworld.org/about-us/history.html |website=Juma's World |publisher=SaveAfricaNow |accessdate=17 June 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150617213603/http://jumasworld.org/about-us/history.html |archivedate=17 June 2015 |df= }}</ref> and produced the documentary film “Africa Sing Me Your Song.” Youngren screened the film to audiences in 2007 and 2008.<ref>{{cite news|last1=This Week|first1=Oshawa|title=Courtice man returns to Durham to spread AIDS awareness|url=http://www.durhamregion.com/news-story/3481313-courtice-man-returns-to-durham-to-spread-aids-awareness/|accessdate=17 June 2015|agency=Oshawa This Week|publisher=Metroland Media|date=February 19, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Site |first1=RTV |title=Raise Their Voice Partners with David Youngren and Save Africa Now |url=http://raisetheirvoice.com/archives/47 |website=Raise Their Voice |publisher=Raise Their Voice |accessdate=17 June 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150617212314/http://raisetheirvoice.com/archives/47 |archivedate=17 June 2015 |df= }}</ref>

In 2012 Youngren released “The Story” which follows a group of volunteers as they travel to [[Tanzania]] to help orphans whose parents have died of [[HIV/AIDS|AIDS]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Garin|first1=Nina|title=PASTOR BRINGS A FILM CREW TO AFRICA TO TELL ‘THE STORY’|url=http://www.utsandiego.com/news/2012/jun/08/tp-pastor-brings-a-film-crew-to-africa-to-tell/|accessdate=17 June 2015|publisher=The San Diego Union Tribune|date=June 8, 2012}}</ref>

In January 2012 Youngren founded Gracewave Church in San Diego.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Arnold|first1=Lori|title=Reel Transformation|url=http://christiannewsjournal.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Chr-Exam-SD-09.12.pdf|accessdate=17 June 2015|issue=Vol. 30, No. 9|publisher=Christian Examiner|date=September 2012}}</ref>

Youngren hosted a radio program and a television program called “Life Without Limits.”<ref>{{cite book|last1=Youngren|first1=David|title=Life From The Inside Out|date=2004|publisher=Harvest International Ministries|isbn=1893301214|pages=129}}<!--|accessdate=17 June 2015--></ref>

