'''JaJuan Latroy Dawson''' (November 5, 1977 – July 12, 2015) was a [[wide receiver]] in the [[NFL]] from 2000 to 2002. He played for the [[Cleveland Browns]] and [[Houston Texans]]. He was drafted by the Browns in the 3rd Round of the [[2000 NFL Draft]] with the 79th overall pick.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/D/DawsJa00.htm|title=JaJuan Dawson|work=Pro-Football-Reference.com}}</ref>
He was a 1995 graduate of [[H.L. Bourgeois High School]] in [[Gray]], [[Louisiana]]. He played collegiately at [[Tulane University]], alongside future NFL quarterbacks [[Shaun King (American football)|Shaun King]] and [[Patrick Ramsey]]. He also played in an offensive system under then [[offensive coordinator|OC]] [[Rich Rodriguez]] in 1997 and 1998.<ref name="sports-reference.com">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/players/jajuan-dawson-1.html |title=JaJuan Dawson |work=College Football at Sports-Reference.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140112194719/http://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/players/jajuan-dawson-1.html |archivedate=2014-01-12 |df= }}</ref>
Dawson was reported to have fallen overboard while on a boating trip with family on July 12, 2015.<ref>http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/houstonchronicle/obituary.aspx?pid=175303753</ref> Reports surfaced that he drowned in [[Lavon Lake]], Texas, and his body was recovered on July 14. Dawson was not wearing a [[lifejacket]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thescoopblog.dallasnews.com/2015/07/search-resumes-for-boater-who-fell-into-lavon-lake.html/|title=Body of former NFL player recovered from Lavon Lake, sheriff’s office says|work=The Scoop Blog|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150713221619/http://thescoopblog.dallasnews.com/2015/07/search-resumes-for-boater-who-fell-into-lavon-lake.html/|archivedate=2015-07-13|df=}}</ref>
==College statistics== *1996: 18 catches for 211 yards and 1 touchdown.<ref name="sports-reference.com"/> *1997: 52 catches for 839 yards and 10 touchdowns. *1998: 74 catches for 1030 yards and 12 touchdowns. *1999: 96 catches for 1051 yards and 8 touchdowns. 1 carry for 3 yards. 14 kick returns for 328 yards.
In 2001, he had 22 catches for 281 yards and 1 touchdown while playing for the [[Cleveland Browns]]. He joined the [[Houston Texans]] in 2002 and had 21 catches for 286 yards.
