'''Léon Aelter''' (born 6 January 1890) was a male [[Sprint (running)|sprinter]] from [[Belgium]].
Aelter competed for his home nation at the [[Athletics at the 1912 Summer Olympics|1912 Summer Olympics]] in [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]]. He finished third in his heat in the [[200 metres]], failing to qualify for the following round. He finished second in his heat in the [[100 metres]] qualifying, qualifying for the semi final, which he was unable to finish.
